      hr
      p.svs
        b elk
        | uses a unique system of removing elements as the screen size gets smaller, a sort of "Mobile Last".
      p.svs For example, hiding an element when on a Laptop resolution will also mean the element is hidden on a Mobile resolution also. This way complexity is reduced when moving down in resolution as opposed to introducing it.

      p Consider,
      .mvs
        script(src="https://gist.github.com/ttxi/ad6737bafd0139a64a8be3222a260126.js")

      p Which produces,

      .row.lvs
        .col-8.hol.mhs.box.vcenter.hcenter
          h6 Laptop or smaller... I disappear.
        .col-4.box.vcenter.hcenter
          b I'm here to stay, forever.

      p The first element inside the row will disappear on a Laptop, but it also won't be present on a Mobile either.
      .row
        .full
          p Similarly you can use 
          code .sod/l/m
          p  to show elements when the user is on a certain device.

      p A caveat of this approach is that elements can not specifically be hidden or shown only on one breakpoint. Hide and Show can also not be used on the same element at the same time.

